<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="474" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,725,858]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,761,786]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1106,761,786]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pondolia">
<emphasis box="[973,1106,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">A. pondolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and was elevated to specific rank by Branch (
<number box="[339,397,798,822]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" value="1998.0">1998</number>
) without comment, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge" box="[728,878,797,822]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" refString="Kluge, A. G. (2001) Gekkotan lizard taxonomy. Hamadryad, 26, 1 - 209." type="journal article" year="2001">
Kluge (
<number box="[812,870,798,822]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
continued to list it as a subspecies. The species is considered Near Threatened (
<bibRefCitation author="Monadjem" box="[481,734,833,858]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" refString="Monadjem, A., Boycott, R. C., Parker, V. &amp; Culverwell, J. (2003) Threatened Vertebrates of Swaziland. Swaziland Red Data Book: Fishes, Amphibians, Reptiles, Birds and Mammals. Ministry of Tourism, Environment and Communications, Swaziland, Mbabane, 256 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Monadjem 
<emphasis box="[611,667,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[674,734,834,858]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Boycott" box="[745,901,834,858]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" refString="Boycott, R. C. (2014). Afroedura major Onderstall, 1984. In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 94." type="journal article" year="2014">
Boycott 
<number box="[840,901,834,858]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
